The paper deals with the construction of Voronoi diagrams, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents algorithms with time and space complexity analysis, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper deals with combinatorial structures, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also presents randomized algorithms, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions applications in VLSI CAD, which is related to cs.GR (Graphics).
